Patch taken from the development of EasyBuild 5.2.2 (?)
Fixes a bug introduced in EasyBuild 5.2.1 where installing Python extensions does not
work with a non-EasyBuild Python as for some reason during that step the proper
EBROOT variable is not set for an external Python module (and cannot be set if the
system Python is used).
diff -Nau easybuild-easyblocks-5.2.1/easybuild/easyblocks/generic/pythonpackage.py.orig easybuild-easyblocks-5.2.1/easybuild/easyblocks/generic/pythonpackage.py
--- easybuild-easyblocks-5.2.1/easybuild/easyblocks/generic/pythonpackage.py.orig	2026-02-20 21:35:58.000000000 +0200
+++ easybuild-easyblocks-5.2.1/easybuild/easyblocks/generic/pythonpackage.py	2026-02-26 19:06:14.000000000 +0200
@@ -919,8 +919,10 @@
                 else:
                     self.log.info("No value set for $CC, so not touching $LDSHARED either")
 
-        # gives CMake a hint for which Python version to use
-        env.setvar("Python3_ROOT_DIR", get_software_root('Python'))
+        # gives CMake a hint for which Python version to use, if a Python dependency is used
+        python_root = get_software_root('Python')
+        if python_root:
+            env.setvar('Python3_ROOT_DIR', python_root)
 
         # creates log entries for python being used, for debugging
         cmd = "%(python)s -V; %(python)s -c 'import sys; print(sys.executable, sys.path)'"
